Governor Mohammed Abdullahi Abubakar has congratulated the Bauchi state Governor-elect, Senator Bala Mohammed on his victory following March 9 governorship election in the state. This was contained in a statement by his Special Adviser on Media and Strategy, Ali M. Ali on Monday. “I congratulate my brother, Sen. Bala on this victory at the polls. “I am delighted to note that in spite of the intensity of the campaigns in our dear state, a peaceful election took place without bloodshed. “Let me therefore invite the Governor-elect to join me in working out the process of a smooth transition. “I sincerely thank the entire people of Bauchi state for their support to my administration and urged them to extend the same to the incoming administration. “I also urge the governor-elect to caution his supporters to be law-abiding while celebrating since the period of campaigns is now over,” Abubakar said. Bala, Ningi’s subtle battle for Bauchi PDP guber ticket 2019 Election: Governor Abubakar, Pate, Bala sign peace accord in Bauchi Governorship candidates, other stakeholders plot APC defeat ‎in Bauchi